                        <seg type="docType">Mortgage.</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_116047">Roche Court (Hampshire)</placeName>. <origDate when="1657">1657, Jan. 27</origDate>. Indenture quadripartite made between (1) Oliver Brocas of North Farham
                        alias Roch Court, Hampshire, gent., and Richard Brocas of St. Paul's Covent
                        Garden, Middlesex, gent., (2) Charles Fox, citizen and Leatherseller of
                        London, and Thomas Evans, citizen and Vintner of London; (3) Simon Benet of
                        Beach Hampton, Buckinghamshire, esq., and (4) Thomas Russell of St. Martin
                        Ludgate, London, gent., being a mortgage by (1) to (3) of the manor of North
                        Farham alias Roch Court, Hampshire, and the manor house called Roch Court
                        and lands in North Farham, together with a schedule of leases (signed and
                        sealed by Oliver Brocas; Richard Brocas; unknown, perhaps Charles Fox or
                        Simon Benet; and Thomas Evans) (endorsed: The Mortgage from Mr Oliver Brocas
                        &amp; Mr Richard Brocas for Â£1534; with a note of dates of payment over
                        three years and amounts payable).</p>
